cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal modeling and verification of safety properties using an SMT model checker. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes an extension of BPMN for data-aware processes. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses partitioning of data into a read-only catalog and a read-write repository. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes an extension of BPMN with additional features. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses an array-based backward reachability procedure for verification, which is a technique commonly used in AI.
